args: This here's the mountain the Mukuroshu\ntold me to come to...
They kidnapped Sazanka AND used a kid\nwhat to lure me here and get the scroll...\nWhat a buncha chumps!
Oh, we're quite accustomed to people\nnot understanding us.
Did you come alone and with the scroll\nas we demanded, warrior?
Whatcha see is whatcha get, pal—\nthough it'd probably be faster to have your\nsecret toadies check if I'm on the level.
You're aware of my clandestine comrades?\nYou are as talented as advertised.
How can I not be? Those cats practically\ngot a bib around their necks with my face\non it what to catch all the drool.
Well then, bring the scroll to me at once\nand we can avoid any unpleasantness.
No, Yachiyo! The scroll is too precious!\nTake it and run!
Ain't no geegaw in the world\nworth a friend's life, Sazanka.
Good, yes. That's an obedient lass. Now...
That there's a speedy unsheathing trick\ncourtesy of my grandpappy. Works great\non saps like you what think I ain't ready.
Take it and make for the Halidom—\nand be sure they send backup!

I'll wait for 'em here and hold 'em off.
Better one of us make off with the goods
than both of us end up on the wrong side
of the dirt!
Then I will be the one to stay!
Leave the rolling around in the mud to a\nmug like me what loves to duel. Now split!
It's in your hands now, Sazanka!

Listen good, ya Mukuroshu rats! From this
moment on, this here's a dueling ground!
So if you want past me, you're gonna have
to send me to the boneyard!
A duel? Oh, but this IS interesting.\nVery well. We shall duel. However...
We will all duel you at once!
Good! The more of you chumps there are,\nthe stronger I get for bumpin' ya off!
She's taken out more of us than I thought\npossible, but she's beginning to tire!
Surrender, warrior. Your sword is not\nenough to stop us, especially when you\nlack the reason and ambition to wield it.
I ain't gonna stand for that kind of talk\nfrom a bunch of mopes like you!
We fight as one because we dream of\nbringing down the shogunate! We wield\nour blades to forge a new and better era!
But you have no dreams! No ideology!\nYou're just a sharp sword and a set of\nfangs cutting down people at random!
Wrong, bub! I fight in order to become\nthe strongest swordswoman ever!
And what do you seek to accomplish\nonce you do?!
(Well, this ain't good... Head's all fuzzy...\nThink I'm slippin' away...)
(Huh? Is this...the old house? Well, I'll be.\nGuess my life's flashing before my eyes.)
(This...is when I left home on my journey,\nafter I couldn't stop all the awful stuff\nwhat went down...)
(Couldn't find a sawbones to cure\nMomoyo... Couldn't stop Saiga from\nhitting the bricks...)
(And I couldn't protect Grandpappy...\nI didn't even know he was in danger!)
(I got all in a tizzy and set out to fulfill his\nwish, but now I think I just wanted to leave\nthat sap version of myself behind...)
(Now it's a memory of my duel with the\nprince! Well, ain't this a kick in the head?)
(In the end, I realized he and me were\npals and ended the duel then and there.)
(But WHY did I do that? Feelings got no\nrole in battle, so why...?)
So what say you hop on the trolley and\nlemme do my duty at their side from this\nday forward, eh?
I'm going to give my sister an unequaled\npiece of armor that will hopefully keep\nher safe...
(Now I get it. The prince is my friend,\nwhich is precious as family. THAT'S why\nI didn't have the sand what to duel him!)
You chose the strength of the sword,\nbut for what purpose do you seek it?
(I get it now. I know why I've been\nchasing this crazy dream all these years.)
This one here is wily indeed.\nBest take her head to be safe.
I finally got a handle on my ambition.\nI know why I'm seekin' power.
How can she even stand\nwith such a wound?!
And because I'm going to become\nthe strongest wielder of it!
Ah, Sazanka... Glad you're here\nfor me at the very end...
Stand back. I'm going to heal her.
She took out this many Mukuroshu\nall by herself?
This is all my fault, Yachiyo. I'm sorry.
Stow that talk, sister. All that matters\nhere is that YOU ain't hurt.
(I think I've finally found the reason\nI want to be strong.)
